In an effort to eliminate the exploitation of the COVID-19 temporary employee relief scheme, the Unemployment Insurance Fund has introduced new stringent controls to verify banking details. UIF Commissioner Teboho Maruping says failure to populate the system properly will lead to more delays in the payment process. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - In a bid to eliminate the exploitation of the COVID-19 temporary employee relief scheme, the Unemployment Insurance Fund (UIF) has introduced stringent controls to verify banking details. UIF Commissioner Teboho Maruping says a failure to populate the system properly, will lead to more delays in the payment process. COVID-19:Â UIF urges claimants to submit correct information "People were able to infiltrate the details of the companies. We've engaged our banking partners so the account details are confirmed at a company level." The commissioner called on companies to verify their details, saying once they have been verified the payments can be carried out more efficiently. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.